                "invention-title": [
                    "Cerium-doped graphite-phase carbon nitride photocatalytic semiconductor material and application thereof",
                    "铈掺杂石墨相氮化碳光催化半导体材料及其应用"
                ]
            },
            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The preparation method comprises the following steps: putting melamine and cerium nitrate hexahydrate into an agate mortar, fully and uniformly grinding, then transferring the mixture powder into a 50ml crucible with a cover, putting the crucible into a muffle furnace, heating to 550 DEG C in an air atmosphere at a heating rate of 15 DEG C/min, keeping the temperature for 2-3 hours, and cooling to room temperature to obtain the cerium-doped graphite-phase carbon nitride photocatalyst. And keeping the temperature at 550 DEG C for 4 hours. And after the reaction is finished, cooling the sample to room temperature, grinding the obtained sample into powder, and collecting to obtain a final light yellow powder sample. The preparation cost is low, the method is simple and environment-friendly, the physical and chemical properties of graphite-phase carbon nitride are improved through rare earth cerium doping, the photocatalytic performance of the graphite-phase carbon nitride is greatly improved, and the preparation method has good application prospects in the fields of photocatalytic hydrogen production, carbon dioxide reduction and pollutant degradation."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本发明公开了一种铈掺杂石墨相氮化碳光催化剂及其应用，其步骤包括将三聚氰胺和六水合硝酸铈放入玛瑙研钵中，充分研磨均匀，然后将混合物粉末转移到50ml带盖坩埚中，再将坩埚放在马弗炉内，在空气气氛中，升温速率为15℃/min，加热到550℃，并保持550℃下4h。反应结束后，样品冷却至室温，所得到的样品被研磨成粉末并收集，得到最终浅黄色粉末样品。本发明制备成本低廉，方法简单，环境友好，并通过稀土铈掺杂改善了石墨相氮化碳的物理和化学性质，极大提高了其光催化性能，在光催化制氢，二氧化碳还原和降解污染物领域具有良好的应用前景。"
                }
            ]
        }
